name: Practice Flow Chart
description:
Be the first Music Geek in your town to get their hands on this high quality 300gsm musical practice flow-chart

"You just finished practicing - Go to bed - Wake up - Keep Practicing"

Perfect for:
Music Geeks, let's face it, we can be a disorganised bunch sometimes.  This will help!
For Music Teachers, sometimes telling students to practice just isn't enough.
Concert bands, music halls and music offices who like to adorn their practice rooms with funny, yet useful, musicy pieces.

name: Swing
description:
Be the first Music Geek in your town to get their hands on this high quality 300gsm Swinging poster, strictly for Music Geeks and hip-cats.

Perfect for:
Music Geeks with a sense of Swinging style, yeah.

For Music Teachers who want to educate their pupils about Duke Ellington-style music.

Concert bands, music halls and music offices who like to adorn their practice rooms with funny wall art.

name: The Science of Sound
description:
Be the first Music Geek in your town to get their hands on this high quality 300gsm poster which shows the musical ranges of different musical instruments and tries to explain the relationship between musical notes and human hearing from a non-linear non-subjective viewpoint.

Perfect for:
Music Geeks who love learning more about music and its relationship with our world.

For Music Teachers of music in general and of Sound Engineering who need a handy poster that can help explain musical range and sound waves.

For Sound Engineers who love to create a vibrant and dynamic sound.

For Sound Engineers who just crank everything up to 11 and make everyone's ears bleed; you know who you are.

Concert bands, music halls and music offices who like to adorn their practice rooms with funny, yet useful, musicy pieces.

name: Circle of Fifths
description:
Be the first Music Geek in your town to get their hands on this high quality 300gsm Tolkien-esque poster.

This poster ask the question "What would music history and music theory textbooks be like if they were written by Tolkien?"

The Circle of Fifths has never been so much fun!
Brilliant as a reference for us Music Geeks who can never remember which key has seven sharps in it.

For Music Teachers to show their pupils that key signatures are not optional, and will be ignored at your peril.

For Tolkien fans who appreciate the complexity of great music.  
Or Medieval dwellers who aren't afraid of the enchanted parchment that spans the whole musical gamut (geddit?)

Concert bands, music halls and music offices who need a ready-reckoner that doubles as a nifty piece of art.

name: The Doctor's Time Signature
description:
Sold under an exclusive license for the UK and EU, we present to you the brilliant musical drawings of Josh Wells from TheOddQuartet.com

No-one else in the whole of the Eastern hemisphere has these posters. 

Be the first Music Geek in your town to get their hands on this high quality 300gsm Doctor Who style poster 
with the infamous quote 
"Wibbly-Wobbly Timey-Wimey"

Perfect for the musically inclined Doctor Who fan, your fellow Whovians will bow to your superior taste in wall decoration. Or for:

Music Geeks can use it to seek the answer to "What it is when a piece goes 1-and-a, 2-and-a...?"
For Music Teachers who want to be down and hip with the kids.
For Whovians who know a good deal when they see it.
Concert bands, music halls and music offices who like to adorn their practice rooms with funny, yet useful, musicy pieces.
